{{afc comment|Wikidata entry [[d:Q11354046]] Wikidata name: mitsutorii [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 08:14, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} {{Distinguish|Three-Pillar Torii}} [[File:Mitsumine Shrine Triple Torii.jpg|thumb|250px|[[Mitsumine Shrine]]'s Mitsutorii]] '''Mitsutorii''' (三ツ鳥居), also called '''Miwa Torii''' (三輪鳥居), is a style of [[torii]], or Shinto gate.
It consists of a central [[Myōjin torii]] flanked by two smaller torii on either side<ref>[[Yutaka Kondo (architectural scholar)|Yutaka Kondo]] (1972). ''Details of Old Architectural Design''. Taiga Publishing.</ref>.
